messageType.name: messageType
messageType.description: Identifies the type of message (trap) being sent. Type types are: 1) command 2) error 3) command log 4) alarm 5) IP log 6) redirect This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

recordId.name: recordId
recordId.description: An ID that is used along with a timestamp, org, host, and application ID to uniquiely identify a message (trap). This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

globalTime.name: globalTime
globalTime.description: The time at which the message was generated, expressed in number of seconds since the epoch (Jan 1, 1970), with respect to GMT. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

localTime.name: localTime
localTime.description: The time at which the message was generated, expressed in number of seconds since the epoch (Jan 1, 1970), with respect to the timezone local to the machine that generated the message. The combination of the globalTime and the localTime can be used to calculate the timezone of the source machine. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

dateString.name: dateString
dateString.description: The date at which the message was generated, with respect to the timezone of the source machine, expressed as an ASCII string in the format yyyy/mm/dd. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

timeString.name: timeString
timeString.description: The time at which the message was generated, with respect to the timezone of the source machine, expressed as an ASCII string in the format hh:mm:ss. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

appId.name: appId
appId.description: The application ID of the NetRanger application that generated the message. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

hostId.name: hostId
hostId.description: The host ID of the machine running the NetRanger application that generated the message. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

orgId.name: orgId
orgId.description: An ID that uniquely identifies the organization responsible for the machine running the NetRanger application that generated the message. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

errorMessage.name: errorMessage
errorMessage.description: Describes the error that occurred. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

sourceAppId.name: sourceAppId
sourceAppId.description: The application ID of the NetRanger application that executed the command. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

sourceHostId.name: sourceHostId
sourceHostId.description: The host ID of the machine running the NetRanger application that executed the command. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

sourceOrgId.name: sourceOrgId
sourceOrgId.description: An ID that uniquely identifies the organization responsible for the machine running the NetRanger application that generated the command. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

commandMessage.name: commandMessage
commandMessage.description: Describes the command that was executed. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

srcDirection.name: srcDirection
srcDirection.description: Describes whether the source of the alarm is inside or outside the protected network. IN means inside, and OUT means outside. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

dstDirection.name: dstDirection
dstDirection.description: Describes whether the destination of the alarm (the machine being attacked) is inside or outside the protected network. IN means inside, and OUT means outside. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

eventLevel.name: eventLevel
eventLevel.description: An integer that reflects the severity level of the alarm. The number can range from 1 to 255, but the current NetRanger system only uses 1 (least severe) to 5 (most severe). This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

sigId.name: sigId
sigId.description: Describes which signature was detected. The full list of signatures can be found on a NetRanger system at /usr/nr/etc/signatures. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

subSigId.name: subSigId
subSigId.description: Provides additional information about an alarm signature. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

protocol.name: protocol
protocol.description: Describes the protocol of the attack that was detected. Usually, this will be TCP/IP. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

srcIpAddr.name: srcIpAddr
srcIpAddr.description: The IP address of the machine from which the attack originated. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

dstIpAddr.name: dstIpAddr
dstIpAddr.description: The IP address of the machine being attacked. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

srcIpPort.name: srcIpPort
srcIpPort.description: The port from which the attack originated. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

dstIpPort.name: dstIpPort
dstIpPort.description: The port that received the attack on the destination machine. This value may not have significance for signatures that involve multiple ports (for example, a port sweep). This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

rtrIpAddr.name: rtrIpAddr
rtrIpAddr.description: The IP address of the router through which the attack traveled. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

alarmMessage.name: alarmMessage
alarmMessage.description: ASCII string that provides additional information about an alarm. For instance, this field gives the exact string that was matched during a string match alarm. This object cannot be retrieved from the SNMP agent.
